    # 3. All three remainders are 2: C(count[2], 3)
    # 4. One remainder is 0, one is 1, and one is 2: count[0] * count[1] * count[2]
    # 5. Two remainders are 1 and one is 2: C(count[1], 2) * count[2]
    # 6. Two remainders are 2 and one is 1: C(count[2], 2) * count[1]

